<div class="markdown"><div class="admonition is-question"><header class="admonition-header">Question:</header><div class="admonition-body"><p>Are there certain colors/combination of colors that should be avoided when presenting visuals?</p></div></div></div>


<div class="markdown"><h4>Color pairs hard for people with CVD</h4><ul><li><p>Red &amp; Green (most common)</p></li><li><p>Blue &amp; Green and Yellow &amp; Red</p></li></ul><h4>Just look bad (very subjective)</h4><ul><li><p>Yellow &amp; Green</p></li><li><p>Brown &amp; Orange</p></li><li><p>Multiple neon colors</p></li></ul><h4>Hard to distinguish</h4><ul><li><p>Yellow &amp; Orange</p></li><li><p>Black &amp; Navy blue</p></li></ul></div>
